-Queue Does Not Allow Random Access
-You can only work with:
front element
rear element
Typical operations:
add() / offer() → insert at rear
remove() / poll() → remove from front
peek() → view front

-3️⃣ Cannot Insert Anywhere
In structures like ArrayList, you can insert anywhere.
Example:
list.add(2, 50);

-5️⃣ Interface Cannot Be Instantiated
Because Queue is an interface, you cannot do:
Queue q = new Queue();   ❌
You must use an implementation:
Queue<Integer> q = new LinkedList<>();

- Deque allows both sides:
