-minStackQuestion
-In Min Stack, the goal is to support `push`, `pop`, `top`, and `getMin` in O(1) time. We solve it using two stacks.
The main stack stores all values normally. The min stack keeps track of the minimum values seen so far.
When pushing a value, also push it to the min stack if it is smaller than or equal to the current minimum.
When popping, if the popped value equals the top of the min stack, remove it from the min stack too. 
The top of the min stack always gives the current minimum instantly.(full on chtgpt @shukla.....com-java masterclass)

-Problem with Normal Queue (Array Implementation)
Suppose queue size = 5
Initial queue:
_ _ _ _ _
Insert elements:
10 20 30 40 50
Now:
Front = 0
Rear = 4
If we remove two elements:
_ _ 30 40 50
But rear is still at index 4, so we cannot insert new elements even though space exists at the beginning.
This causes wasted space.
Condition for Full Queue:-
Queue is full when:
(rear + 1) % size == front
Example:
size = 5
rear = 4
(4 + 1) % 5 = 0

